cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM 

This paper is about crowd counting, which is a computer vision task. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also introduces a new architecture that is discovered through Neural Architecture Search (NAS), which falls under the category of machine learning and optimization. Hence, cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are also likely sub-categories. Additionally, the paper proposes a novel loss function, which involves multi-scale supervision, and this could be relevant to the sub-categories of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.MM (Multimedia).
